Web Application Architecture
===========================
Front End
	-web page 	: html , jsp  			: page layout
			: css, bootstrap			: beauty
			: js, jquery, ajax			: client side action
			: jqury -library of java sccript 
			: difference between html and jsp 
			-html : hyertext markup language : static contnets
			-jsp : java server page : dynamic content 
			      :jsp can contains java code within html tag 
			
	-Server Side coding/Language
			-php
			-java /servlet	: is extension java class which provider http 	
				handler (http request handling features)
				HttRequest (is class) : read and get html/web request 	

				content/data 
				HttpResponse (is class) : send content/reponse to web 	

			page /web browser 


			-c#
			-python 			 				

Back End: is database 
		-My SQL Server
		-MS SQL Server
		-Oracle
		etc.
		
	
		

Client Server Architecture
==============================
Client : web browser	to access the web applicaton / open web application
	-IE
	-Chrome
	-Mozilla
	-Opera
	etc.
Server : web server   - to develop and host/deploy web application 
	-Apahce Tomcat
	-GlassFish 
	-Wamp
	-Xamp
	-Lamp
	-JBoss
	etc.

	

Http: hypertext transfer protocal which is responsiable to send the request from web browser to 

web server and recieve the reponse from webserver to web browser 
================


-Servlet Life cycle
	-dispatcher
	-sendredirect
=========================
doGet()
doPost()

<form  action="toservlet"  
		default is : get 		:data will send in url/querysting
		method=""  : get		:data will send in url/querysting
		method="get"  : get		:data will send in url/querysting
			-get can bookmark
			-get can send to other web application 
				example : login with gmail, facebook

		method="post"  : post	: data will send in body/will be hidden	
			-confidential / pwd /secure
			-alot of data 
				


JSP vs Servlet 
=================
Jsp : is java server page 
	: html file where java code can be embeded
Servlet :
	-java file to handle the http request
	-java file/code where html code can be embeded
	
State Management : web applications work on http protocal which is stateless
====================
There are following way to manage state of data:
-client side
	-cookies		: applicaiton level within browser
			: example: rember pwd
	-hidden field	: page level
	-cache 		: page level , event level
-server side
	-session 		: applicaiton level server / will work like global variable 



-web-inf
	-lib
		-all library of java applications
-web.xml	: is configuration file
	-welcome page / startup page / landling page
	-session timeout
	
		
-context : is global variable which can access from anywhere within application 

		

